Entertainment & Media: The Department of Justice stated that Google should have to sell off its Chrome browser to address the monopolization of the online search market, causing communication services stocks to fall by nearly 2%[1]. This development could have broader implications for tech and media companies.

Financial Services: Fundstrat's Tom Lee predicts that bitcoin can hit "well above" $100,000 before year-end, potentially impacting cryptocurrency-related financial services[2]. Additionally, China bonds rallied with the 10-year yield hitting a multi-decade low on rate cut expectations, which could affect global financial markets[2].

